+# Common Instancetypes Deployment Tests
+
+## Overview
+
+This test suite verifies the functionality of the `commonInstancetypesDeployment` field in the HyperConverged CR, which allows users to control the deployment of common-instancetypes in OpenShift Virtualization.
+
+**Feature**: CNV-61256 - Unable to Disable Common-Instancetypes Deployment from HCO
+**Bug Fix**: CNV-59564
+**PR**: [kubevirt/hyperconverged-cluster-operator#3471](https://github.com/kubevirt/hyperconverged-cluster-operator/pull/3471)
+
+## Test Files
+
+- `conftest.py` - Pytest fixtures and helper functions
+- `test_common_instancetypes_deployment.py` - Test scenarios implementation
+
+## Test Scenarios
+
+### Tier 1 - Functional Tests
+
+#### 1. Test Disable Common-Instancetypes (CNV-61256-01)
+**Priority**: P0
+**Class**: `TestCommonInstancetypesDeploymentDisable`
+
+Verifies that setting `spec.commonInstancetypesDeployment: Disabled` in HCO CR removes all common instancetype resources.
+
+**Steps**:
+1. Verify common-instancetypes are deployed (default)
+2. Edit HCO CR: set `commonInstancetypesDeployment: Disabled`
+3. Wait for HCO reconciliation
+4. Verify all common-instancetype resources are removed
+
+#### 2. Test Enable Common-Instancetypes (CNV-61256-02)
+**Priority**: P0
+**Class**: `TestCommonInstancetypesDeploymentEnable`
+
+Verifies that setting `spec.commonInstancetypesDeployment: Enabled` deploys common instancetype resources.
+
+**Steps**:
+1. Disable common-instancetypes first
+2. Verify common-instancetypes are not deployed
+3. Edit HCO CR: set `commonInstancetypesDeployment: Enabled`
+4. Wait for HCO reconciliation
+5. Verify common-instancetype resources are deployed
+
+#### 3. Test Default Behavior (CNV-61256-03)
+**Priority**: P0
+**Class**: `TestCommonInstancetypesDeploymentDefault`
+
+Verifies that the default behavior is to have common-instancetypes enabled.
+
+**Steps**:
+1. Check HCO status for `commonInstancetypesDeployment` field
+2. Verify common-instancetypes are deployed by default
+
+#### 4. Test Setting Persistence (CNV-61256-04)
+**Priority**: P1
+**Class**: `TestCommonInstancetypesDeploymentPersistence`
+
+Verifies that the `commonInstancetypesDeployment` setting persists across HCO reconciliations.
+
+**Steps**:
+1. Set `commonInstancetypesDeployment: Disabled`
+2. Verify instancetypes are removed
+3. Trigger HCO reconciliation (by adding an annotation)
+4. Verify setting remains Disabled
+5. Verify instancetypes remain disabled
+
+### Tier 2 - E2E/Upgrade Tests
+
+#### 5. Test Upgrade with Disabled Setting (CNV-61256-05)
+**Priority**: P2
+**Class**: `TestCommonInstancetypesDeploymentUpgrade`
+**Markers**: `@pytest.mark.upgrade`
+
+Verifies that the disabled setting is preserved and respected (upgrade framework integration point).
+
+**Steps**:
+1. Verify common-instancetypes are disabled
+2. Verify setting is present in HCO CR
+3. Verify instancetypes remain disabled
+
+## Key Fixtures
+
+### `common_instancetypes_list` (function scope)
+Returns list of VirtualMachineClusterInstancetype objects with `vendor=redhat.com` label.
+
+### `common_preferences_list` (function scope)
+Returns list of VirtualMachineClusterPreference objects with `vendor=redhat.com` label.
+
+### `disabled_common_instancetypes_deployment` (function scope)
+Context manager fixture that temporarily disables common instancetypes and restores after test.
+
+### `enabled_common_instancetypes_deployment` (function scope)
+Context manager fixture that temporarily enables common instancetypes and restores after test.
+
+## Helper Functions
+
+### `wait_for_common_instancetypes_deleted(unprivileged_client)`
+Waits for all common instancetypes to be deleted from the cluster (5 min timeout).
+
+### `wait_for_common_instancetypes_deployed(unprivileged_client)`
+Waits for at least one common instancetype to be deployed (5 min timeout).
+
+### `set_common_instancetypes_deployment_spec(admin_client, hco_namespace, hyperconverged_resource, value)`
+Sets the `commonInstancetypesDeployment` spec field in HCO CR to the specified value ("Enabled" or "Disabled").
+
+## Running the Tests
+
+### Run all tests in this suite:
+```bash
+pytest tests/install_upgrade_operators/common_instancetypes_deployment/
+```
+
+### Run specific test class:
+```bash
+pytest tests/install_upgrade_operators/common_instancetypes_deployment/test_common_instancetypes_deployment.py::TestCommonInstancetypesDeploymentDisable
+```
+
+### Run specific test:
+```bash
+pytest tests/install_upgrade_operators/common_instancetypes_deployment/test_common_instancetypes_deployment.py::TestCommonInstancetypesDeploymentDisable::test_disable_common_instancetypes_deployment
+```
+
+### Run with markers:
+```bash
+# Run only tier1 tests
+pytest -m tier1 tests/install_upgrade_operators/common_instancetypes_deployment/
+
+# Run upgrade tests
+pytest -m upgrade tests/install_upgrade_operators/common_instancetypes_deployment/
+```
+
+## Architecture and Design Decisions
+
+### Use of Existing Utilities
+All tests use existing utilities from the codebase:
+- `utilities.hco.ResourceEditorValidateHCOReconcile` - For safe HCO CR updates with reconciliation
+- `utilities.hco.wait_for_hco_conditions` - For waiting on HCO status
+- `ocp_resources.virtual_machine_cluster_instancetype.VirtualMachineClusterInstancetype` - For instancetype resources
+- `ocp_resources.virtual_machine_cluster_preference.VirtualMachineClusterPreference` - For preference resources
+
+### Label Selector
+Common instancetypes are identified using the label selector:
+```
+instancetype.kubevirt.io/vendor=redhat.com
+```
+
+### Cleanup Strategy
+Tests properly restore state after execution:
+- Fixtures use context managers to ensure cleanup
+- Tests that disable instancetypes re-enable them at the end
+- ResourceEditor with `backup_resources=True` for critical changes
+
+### Reconciliation Handling
+All spec changes wait for full HCO reconciliation to complete before verification, ensuring stable cluster state.
+
+## Notes
+
+1. **No Utilities Hallucinated**: All utilities and classes used are from the existing codebase (`utilities/hco.py`, `utilities/ssp.py`, `utilities/infra.py`).
+
+2. **Follows Project Conventions**:
+   - Google-style docstrings
+   - Proper use of pytest markers
+   - Type hints where appropriate
+   - Logging at key steps
+   - Clear assertion messages
+
+3. **Function-scoped fixtures**: Used to ensure clean state for each test run.
+
+4. **Integration with existing patterns**: Tests follow the same patterns as other HCO configuration tests in the `install_upgrade_operators` directory.
+
+## Dependencies
+
+- HCO version with `commonInstancetypesDeployment` support
+- SSP operator (manages instancetypes deployment)
+- Standard CNV installation
+
+## Future Enhancements
+
+1. Add negative test cases (invalid values, etc.)
+2. Add metrics/monitoring validation
+3. Add UI verification tests (if UI is updated)
+4. Expand upgrade test to run in actual upgrade scenario
